definition: to move/to shift/to change (a position or location etc)/to promote
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]

sentences.english: The newly married couple moved into their new home.
sentences.chinese: 這對新婚夫婦遷入新居。

sentences.english: Among the migrant tribes who settled in the region were the Amorites.
sentences.chinese: 在遷移的部族當中，遷入那個地區的是亞摩利人。

sentences.english: In 2014, UM made complete relocation to the new campus.
sentences.chinese: 2014年，澳門大學整體遷入新校園。

sentences.english: Next year, we will open our new Embassy compound in Beijing.
sentences.chinese: 明年，我國駐北京大使館將遷入新址。

sentences.english: Policy-holder change is gone to other place, if ingoing ground already built system of social endowment insurance.
sentences.chinese: 投保人遷往外地，若遷入地已建立社會養老保險制度。

sentences.english: After physical changes of any kind, immigration will have been prevented.
sentences.chinese: 起了任何性質的物理變化之後，遷入也要受到防礙。

sentences.english: America is the most notable example, because it has seen the most in-migration.
sentences.chinese: 美國是最著名的例子，因爲它看到了最大的遷入。

sentences.english: Schools help to acculturate the second generation of immigrants.
sentences.chinese: 學校有助於使移民的第二代適應遷入國的文化習俗。

sentences.english: Most of them moved into Southeast Asia and Japan.
sentences.chinese: 遷入地以東南亞和日本爲主。

sentences.english: My grandmother wept the day we moved in.
sentences.chinese: 在我們遷入新居的那天祖母流了淚。

sentences.english: We had water and gas laid on before moved into our new home.
sentences.chinese: 我們叫人安裝了自來水和煤氣以後才遷入新居。

sentences.english: The children of immigrants have come to acculturate.
sentences.chinese: 移民的孩子們已逐漸適應遷入國的文化習俗。
